(xx)  submit reports as specified in the reporting requirements listed below.  

2.  Gender and Development Specialists (3 domestic, 24 person-months total) 

5.   The specialists will 

(i)  help the team leader to prepare a work program for the TA; 
(ii)  support  WEDs  in  preparing  an  inventory  of  women  in  LRBs  and  of  future 
candidates of women in LRBs, and identify best practices for women in politics; 
(iii)  compile training materials from NGOs and research institutions on women in 
politics; 
(iv)  identify NGOs and research institutions to train women candidates and women in 
LRBs, prepare a training program, and provide training as needed;  
(v)  prepare a training program for WEDs based on their needs and conduct training; 
(vi)  prepare a gender analysis of the local budgets, in cooperation with WEDs; 
(vii)  recommend ways to institutionalize gender responsive budgeting; 
(viii)  conduct workshops in selected villages in the three districts on budget literacy 
and  other  related  issues,  including  developing  mechanisms  for  community 
participation in the planning and development decision-making processes; 
(ix)  in cooperation with the team leader, analyze the proposed TA reform program 
and prepare recommendations on how to mainstream gender in the program; 
(x)  consult with stakeholders regarding the national action plan; and 
(xi)  carry out other activities as assigned by the team leader.   

3.  NGOs for Training Activities (6 domestic person-months) 

6.  Allowance has been made for 6 domestic person-months, to be allocated as required to 
engage NGOs to conduct training activities.
